The Governments of the Netherlands nationalize part of the Fortis Bank.
The Netherlands states - being the first in Europe - will help with a nationalisation to the Belgian-Dutch bank Fortis which is in distress due to the effect of the mortgage crisis of the American market: the three countries will support in total with 11,2 billion euros to this financial and insurance institution that also has business in Hungary.
This weekend the governments of Belgium, Luxembourg and the Netherlands held consultations at the highest level with the President of the European Central Bank and the responsible for the economic competition of the European Commission.
The Fortis Bank is the first to suffer from the crisis in the Euro area in the context of the international financial crisis that has been taking place in several waves more than a year ago, so the decisions taken with regard to the Bank, in a sense, can be regarded as precedents.
According to the decision taken on Sunday morning, the three States will purchase approximately half (49 per cent) of the Bank's property in its area.
The Bank will certainly sell a portion of its business, including mainly insurance activities purchased last year by the Dutch ABN Amró.
The actions of Fortis began a sharp decline last week and for the second half of the week there were already important signs of crisis in the institution.
However, analysts agree to point out that with its 85,000 employees this Bank is too large to allow it to break down.
The company's shares only decreased by 12 percent on Friday, being the lowest in the last 14 years.
Since January the value of the shares has decreased by more than two thirds.
Observing the current prices of the shares, the total value of the group's capital on the market is around 14 billion euros, but according to the company's executives this is not real.
The Bank's management attributed the sharp fall in Fortis' shares to the insecurity of the US market in connection with the approval of the $700 billion US package plan.
On Monday the shares already showed a slight increase.
On Friday they appointed Filip Dierckx as the new general manager of the bank.
The Bank also sought private investors, but so far no one has given a concrete offer.
The Belgian government had already ensured that investors did not have to worry, they will not lose their money.
Among the Bank's clients so far there was no panic, they did not invade the bank offices to withdraw their money.
The Fortis has its own branch office in Hungary and has also purchased leasing companies.
Zorro in the henhouse
In the United States, life and health insurance companies, when they see data on the purchase of medication, often refuse to sign an insurance contract.
Privacy policy specialists fear that the personal data market will become uncontrollable.
"There are programs for the protection of personal data, which to the use of prescription data in all cases binds it to the approval of the given person.
The same must be in independent hands, because if not, "we trust the chicken to the fox" - quotes the Washington Post to Richard Dick, designer of the medical prescription tracking program.
Insurance companies make the price of insurance and the amount of compensation for the customer's health and if they believe that the risk is excessive, they simply do not make the contract.
They first sent the client to medical check-up and signed the contract with him already knowing the result of the check-up.
Dick ten years ago invented a much cheaper procedure: with the customer identification number he easily obtains from the pharmacies the list of medicines purchased in the last year and a half and the program itself draws the conclusion on the client's disease and health status.
For example, if you systematically take large doses of cholesterol-lowering pills, it indicates that the level of fat in your blood is virtually incurably high, so you are immediately included in a higher risk category.
They circulate numerous versions of the program, some even set a risk number, so the insurance company in addition to the administration has little to do, although there are small difficulties in this regard.
Among the program's disadvantages is, for example, that some drugs are multi-use, for example, certain substances serve both to treat headache and heat waves and even as antidepressants.
The latter is an important risk enhancement factor for insurance companies while the former are not.
Special companies were set up to consult and process these data, which, before acquiring the necessary information from the pharmacies, request the patient's approval.
The authorities are already forcing them to do this, although they have not received a fine for negligence so far.
Some companies have also recently developed the results of laboratory tests and combined them with drug use data obtain more accurate information about the patient's health status.
More and more companies have access to these data and simultaneously it is increasingly difficult to control their use.
There is an exclusive law for the protection of personal health data, but it applies only to insurance companies and those providing health services.
Congress already has before it the bill that gives the authority for the control of specialized companies for the provision of personal data.
Dick Richard acknowledges that this is insufficient: therefore he developed his program, which will require the specific approval of the person for the provision of his own personal data.
It is another matter that this person cannot deny his approval, because if not the insurance companies will not sign the contract with him.
So the chickens, despite everything, are exposed to the good will of the fox.
